1 AN ACT relating to workforce development, making an appropriation therefor, and
2 declaring an emergency.
3 Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of Kentucky:
4 SECTION 1. A NEW SECTION OF KRS CHAPTER 336 IS CREATED TO
5 READ AS FOLLOWS:
6 As used in Sections 1 to 3 of this Act:
7 (1) "Apprentice" means a person employed by a public water or wastewater system
8 who is enrolled in a registered apprenticeship program for water systems
9 operations specialists or wastewater systems operations specialists, who has
10 entered into a voluntary written agreement with the registered apprenticeship
11 program sponsor, and that agreement has been submitted to the United States
12 Department of Labor's Office of Apprenticeship and the Kentucky Apprenticeship
13 Council;
14 (2) "Cabinet" means the Education and Labor Cabinet;
15 (3) "Employer" means any person or organization employing an apprentice whether
16 or not the employer is a party to an apprenticeship agreement or on-the-job
17 training agreement with the apprentice;
18 (4) "Kentucky FLOW Program" means the Kentucky Future Leaders of Water
19 Program established in Section 2 of this Act;
20 (5) "Public water or wastewater system" means:
21 (a) A water district or joint water commission formed under KRS Chapter 74;
22 (b) A water association formed as a nonprofit corporation under KRS Chapter
23 273;
24 (c) A sewer district, sanitation district, or joint sewer agency formed under KRS
25 Chapter 65, 67, 76, or 220;
26 (d) A regional wastewater commission formed under KRS Chapter 65;
27 (e) A municipal water utility or water works, sewer utility, sewage system or
Page 1 of 7
